SP  - 139-150
DO  - 10.1016/j.cger.2025.08.007
AB  - The article discusses the challenges and strategies for managing chronic pain in  homebound older adults. It highlights the high prevalence of chronic pain in this  population and the barriers to accessing pain care, such as mobility issues and  transportation difficulties. The document emphasizes the importance of an  interprofessional, integrative approach to pain management, including  nonpharmacologic treatments like cognitive behavioral therapy and physical  therapy, as well as careful consideration of pharmacologic options. It also calls  for policy changes to improve access to pain care and further research to address  the unmet needs of homebound older adults with chronic pain.
