T1  - [Give general practitioner a central role during the chronic phase after stroke].
SP  - A7865
AB  - In February 2014 an update of a systematic review was published on the  effectiveness of physical therapy after stroke. This review shows that the  quality and quantity of the scientific basis for physical therapy interventions  in rehabilitation after stroke have increased significantly, which confirms the  relevance of physical therapy in multidisciplinary stroke care. As far as  physical therapy is concerned, implementation of the results of this review and  organisation or reorganisation of care so that it is accessible to all patients  is a major challenge. We propose that the general practitioner should be given a  central role in the care of patients during the chronic phase after stroke.
