IS  - 3
Y1  - 1988 Sep 1
T1  - Conservative management of low back pain. An evaluation of current methods.
SP  - 127-33
AB  - The overwhelming majority of patients with low back pain recover, most of them  within 6 to 12 weeks. Those who do not, however, represent a major challenge to  physicians, who need to choose from among the many therapies for low back pain  that have been advocated but in many cases not proven. For those with chronic low  back pain, a functional restoration program and a multidisciplinary pain  management program may prove effective.
